# Code Chronicles — Project Overview

**What**: A personal technical blog and learning platform by Sandeep Reddy Alalla.
**URL**: https://blog.sandeepallala.com
**Hosting**: Netlify (auto-deploys from `main` branch)

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router) with TypeScript
- **Content**: MDX files with YAML frontmatter, compiled via `next-mdx-remote`
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS with dark mode (class-based), custom violet palette
- **Syntax highlighting**: Shiki
- **Path alias**: `@/*` maps to project root

## Directory Structure

```
app/            → Next.js pages and API routes
components/     → Reusable React components
content/        → Blog posts (MDX), courses (JSON), challenges (JSON), quizzes (JSON)
lib/            → Core utilities (mdx.ts, courses.ts, challenges.ts, quiz.ts, publishing.ts)
scripts/        → Automation scripts (post-to-x.ts, post-to-linkedin.ts, publish-scheduled.ts)
data/           → Running/fitness data (Garmin sync)
.cursor/skills/ → Agent Skills (blog-writer, content-leverage-engine, staff-prep-daily)
```

## Key Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `lib/mdx.ts` | MDX compilation, frontmatter parsing, reading time, draft filtering |
| `lib/courses.ts` | Course metadata loading, post grouping by course/module |
| `lib/challenges.ts` | Challenge JSON loading |
| `lib/publishing.ts` | Scheduled publishing, draft management |
| `next.config.ts` | `trailingSlash: false` for stable canonical URLs |
| `netlify.toml` | Build config, www→non-www 301 redirect |

## Content Counts (as of Feb 2026)

- 15 published blog posts, 3 drafts
- 3 courses: `javascript`, `html-css`, `low-level-design`
- 3 coding challenges: classnames, debounce, DOM manipulation

## Important Conventions

- Author is always "Sandeep Reddy Alalla"
- Site URL constant: `https://blog.sandeepallala.com`
- Drafts live in `content/blog/drafts/` with `draft: true`; production hides them
- Published posts live in `content/blog/` with `draft: false`
